        "description": "Followup to ARROW-8379, which set use_threads = FALSE on Windows. See discussion about adding more controls, disabling threading in some places and not others, etc. We want to do this soon after release so that we have a few months to see how things behave on CI before releasing again.\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nCollecting some CI hangs after ARROW-8379\r\n\r\n1. Rtools35, 64bit test suite hangs: \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/11290/checks?check_run_id=3767787034\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n** running tests for arch 'i386' ...\r\n  Running 'testthat.R' [17s]\r\n OK\r\n** running tests for arch 'x64' ...\r\n\r\nError: Error: <rlib_error_2_0 in process_get_error_connection(self, private):\r\n stderr is not a pipe.>\r\n{code}",
